[1] Canada (Alberta)
Date: Mon 3 Nov 2014
Source: 660 News [edited]
http://www.660news.com/2014/11/03/enterovirus-d-68-cases-increase/


The number of enterovirus D-68 cases continues to climb in the province. Alberta Health Services [AHS] says there are now 111 confirmed patients with the virus, up 18 since the last report in mid-October 2014.

Over half of those cases are in Calgary, where 60 people have been infected.

AHS is reminding Albertans to help fight off getting sick by washing hands regularly, keeping hands away from faces, staying home when sick, and avoiding people who are coughing and sneezing.

[Byline: Mike Tarasko]

