******
[2] Canada (Prince Edward Island)
Date: Thu 30 Oct 2014
Source: CBC News, Prince Edward Island (P.E.I.) [edited]
http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/prince-edward-island/second-case-of-enterovirus-confirmed-in-province-1.2818250


Two children on P.E.I have had confirmed cases of enterovirus. Health P.E.I. officials say both children have been released now from hospital. They said both children are under the age of ten. Officials said the children are doing well.

The 1st case on the island was reported earlier this month [October 2014]. Only hospitalized cases in P.E.I. with respiratory illness are being tested for EV-D68. The virus usually causes mild respiratory infections and cold-like illnesses. It can be spread through coughing and sneezing or by close contact with infected persons. Health officials note most people who become ill with the virus will recover at home, but anyone experiencing difficulty breathing or shortness of breath should see a doctor.

